        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p><strong>Search everywhere optimization</strong> is the practice of making your brand discoverable wherever people search — not just Google, but also ChatGPT, TikTok, YouTube, Reddit, Amazon, and voice assistants like Siri and Alexa. In 2025, 46% of Gen Z starts product research on TikTok or Instagram. AI chatbots handle 100M+ queries weekly. Focusing only on Google means missing where a growing share of your audience actually looks for answers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Gen Z social search</div>
            <div class="tms-value">46% start on TikTok/IG</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">CRO / Multi-Platform</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Google share decline</div>
            <div class="tms-value">2–3% annually</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Difficulty</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Intermediate</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">Traditional SEO optimized for one channel when Google owned 90%+ of search behavior. That reality has shifted. Queries haven't disappeared — they've spread. Search everywhere optimization is the framework for capturing demand wherever it now lives.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is search everywhere optimization?</h2>
        <p>Search everywhere optimization (sometimes abbreviated SEO² or multi-platform SEO) is a discovery strategy that extends beyond Google's organic results to every digital surface where people actively search for answers, products, or services.</p>
        <p>The core insight: search behavior is platform-agnostic, but most SEO budgets are not. People search on YouTube the way they search on Google. They search within TikTok's discovery feed. They ask ChatGPT instead of typing a query. They scroll Reddit threads the way they would read a comparison article. Each platform has its own index and ranking system — and each requires a different optimization approach.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">The platform shift is measurable</div>
          <p>Google's share of initial search intent is declining by 2–3% annually. AI chatbots handle 100M+ queries weekly. Reddit ranks on page one for 97.5% of keyword categories. YouTube has 2B+ monthly logged-in users. The queries haven't disappeared — they've spread.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why search everywhere optimization matters in 2026</h2>
        <p>Three structural shifts make multi-platform search optimization necessary rather than optional:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Generational search behavior change.</strong> 46% of Gen Z starts product research on TikTok or Instagram — not Google. This cohort is entering peak purchasing power. Ignoring social search now means starting from zero when they become your primary customers.</li>
          <li><strong>AI absorption of informational queries.</strong> ChatGPT and Perplexity have absorbed millions of informational queries that used to generate organic Google clicks. A brand that is not cited by AI systems is invisible for an entire class of queries.</li>
          <li><strong>Reddit and community content are now a SERP feature.</strong> Reddit ranks on page one for 97.5% of keyword categories. Google actively surfaces Reddit threads in search results. If competitors have established community presence and you do not, they capture intent you cannot see in rank trackers.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How search everywhere optimization works</h2>
        <p>This is a framework for distributing content across every platform where your audience searches — not a single tactic.</p>

        <h3>Step 1 — Map your audience's actual search behavior</h3>
        <p>Before creating a single piece of content, identify where your specific audience researches. B2B buyers research on Google, LinkedIn, and YouTube. Local consumers check Google, TikTok, and Instagram. E-commerce shoppers use Amazon, Google, and TikTok. The platform mix varies dramatically by audience and intent type.</p>

        <h3>Step 2 — Create platform-native content</h3>
        <p>A blog post optimized for Google will not perform on TikTok without adaptation. Each platform rewards different formats: short-form video for social search, long-form structured articles for organic search, structured FAQ pages for AI retrieval, community answers for Reddit. Native content outperforms repurposed content on every platform's algorithm.</p>

        <h3>Step 3 — Build cross-platform authority signals</h3>
        <p>AI systems and social algorithms both reward authority signals. Backlinks help on Google. Engagement helps on social. Brand mentions across platforms help everywhere. A consistent content presence across multiple platforms compounds visibility in ways that single-channel optimization cannot replicate.</p>

        <h3>Step 4 — Track discovery across channels</h3>
        <p>Traditional rank tracking only covers Google. Search everywhere optimization requires monitoring AI visibility, social search impressions, YouTube rankings, and Reddit mentions. You need a multi-platform dashboard, not just a rank tracker.</p>

        <h2 id="types">Types of search everywhere optimization</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Type</th><th>Platforms</th><th>Key Signal</th><th>Priority</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
